Architecture: x86_64
Operating System: Linux (tested on Debian 11 / Ubuntu 20.04+)
Storage: ~2 GB for Docker image, ~500 MB for artifact

=== Docker Image (recommended) ===

Pre-built Docker image available on Docker Hub:
  docker pull wangshaohao/mgo-ae:latest

Alternatively, build from source (included in the artifact):
  docker build -t mgo-ae .

The image contains:
  - CBMC 5.12 (installed via Debian package)
  - GenMC v0.9 (compiled from source with LLVM 11.0.1)
  - Nidhugg 0.4 (compiled from source with LLVM 11.0.1)
  - Clang 11.0.1 (for generating LLVM IR files)
  - All 58 benchmark files and evaluation scripts under /benchmarks/

=== IRhunter (separate setup) ===

IRhunter is composed of two components:
  - UFO (dynamic instrumentation engine): Docker image "4ndychin/llvm-ufo"
    (provided by IRhunter authors, LLVM 7.1.0 with modified ThreadSanitizer)
  - reorder-main (reordering prediction engine): Maven-based Java 8 project
    (included under Evaluation/IRhunter/)

Additional IRhunter dependencies:
  - Docker (for UFO container)
  - Maven + JDK 8 (for reorder-main)

=== Dependencies ===

  - Docker 20.10+ (for running all tools)
  - Bash (for all automation scripts)
  - Maven + JDK 8 (for IRhunter reorder-main only)
